subsection.def:
agent
                    (代理人) means a person appointed as an agent in
                accordance with section 7;

class
                    (類別), in relation to a local vessel, means a
                class of local vessel specified in column 1 of Schedule 1;

type
                    (類型), in relation to a local vessel, means a
                type of local vessel specified in column 2 of Schedule 1;

paragraph.content:
the original owner and the new owner of the vessel shall sign a notice of
                    transfer of ownership in duplicate (one copy for the original owner and the
                    other for the new owner);

subparagraph.content:
a full licence, temporary licence or permission for a laid-up vessel,
                        if its amendment is necessary for reflecting the change so notified;
                        and

paragraph.content:
a temporary permit to remain in the waters of Hong Kong issued under
                        regulation 7 of the repealed Launches and Ferry Vessels
                    Regulations;

a temporary operating permit in lieu of a licence or permit issued under
                        regulation 8 of the repealed Launches and Ferry Vessels
                    Regulations;

schedule.text:
On the
            north—The
            shoreline of Kowloon and the New Territories;

On the
            south—The
            shoreline of Hong Kong Island;
